Winter Olympics 1992:
   Games Stats: Crowds
-- Ratio of police to athletes at the 1976 Innsbruck
Games:  2 to 1.
                                                                                                       

   -- Record number of spectators attending a single event:
150,000 (ski jump at 1952 Oslo Games).
                                                                                                       

   -- Proportion of seats at any Albertville event that will
go to actual ticket holders: less than 50% (majority will go
to non-paying athletes, officials, sponsors, journalists and
VIPs).
                                                                                                       

   -- Means of applause used by spectators at ancient games
(720 B.C. to 394 A.D.): snorting and lip-smacking.
                                                                                                       

   Compiled by Olympic Factbook, Visible Ink Press, a divison
of Gale Research, Detroit